        "id": "8YN66_y1MhRg"
      },
      "source": [
        "#  **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA):**\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Univariate Analysis:**\n",
        " Each column was analyzed individually to understand its distribution and characteristics. This revealed insights such as:\n",
        " -   The most frequent host cities (Mumbai, Kolkata, Delhi).\n",
        "-    The common toss decision (fielding first).\n",
        "-    The rarity of tied or no-result matches.\n",
        "-   The top teams by participation and wins.\n",
        "-   The leading \"Man of the Match\" award winners.\n",
        "  \n",
        "\n",
        "2. **Bivariate & Multivariate Analysis**: Relationships between multiple variables were explored to uncover deeper patterns:\n",
        "-   Analysis of toss decisions against match outcomes showed a slight advantage for teams choosing to field first.\n",
        "-   The correlation between winning the toss and winning the match was found to be marginal, indicating that while advantageous, it's not a decisive factor.\n",
        "Overall, wins by chasing (wickets) were more frequent than wins by defending (runs), reinforcing the preference for fielding first.\n",
        "-   The consistent strong performance of franchises like Mumbai Indians and Chennai Super Kings across seasons was highlighted."
      ]
