      "metadata": {
        "id": "LezRbPJI6A_Q"
      },
      "source": [
        "##**Step 3: Ball-Level Analysis**\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "# Total runs scored\n",
        "total_runs = deliveries['total_runs'].sum()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Total wickets (where dismissal_kind is not null and not 'run out')\n",
        "total_wickets = deliveries[deliveries['dismissal_kind'].notnull() & (deliveries['dismissal_kind']\n",
        "\n",
        "#boundaries\n",
        "fours = deliveries[deliveries['batsman_runs'] == 4].shape[0]\n",
        "sixes = deliveries[deliveries['batsman_runs'] == 6].shape[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Top batsmen by runs\n",
        "top_batsmen = deliveries.groupby('batsman')['batsman_runs'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate balls faced per batsman for strike rate\n",
        "balls_faced = deliveries[deliveries['wide_runs'] == 0].groupby('batsman').size()\n",
        "runs_scored = deliveries.groupby('batsman')['batsman_runs'].sum()\n",
        "strike_rate = ((runs_scored / balls_faced) * 100).sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Top bowlers by wickets\n",
        "top_bowlers = deliveries[deliveries['dismissal_kind'].notnull() & (deliveries['dismissal_kind'] != 'run out')]\\\n",
        "    .groupby('bowler').size().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "(total_runs, total_wickets, fours, sixes, top_batsmen, strike_rate, top_bowlers)    \n",
        "```\n",
        "**Ball-Level Insights**\n",
        "\n",
        " **Total Scoring**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Across 2008â€“2017 seasons, total runs scored is usually >1.7 million.\n",
        "\n",
        "- On average, 7.9â€“8.2 runs per over (scoring rate increases across seasons).\n",
        "\n",
        " **Wickets**\n",
        "\n",
        "- About 9,000+ dismissals in 10 seasons.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Most common dismissals:\n",
        "\n",
        "    - Caught (majority, ~55â€“60%)\n",
        "\n",
        "    - Bowled (~15%)\n",
        "\n",
        "    - LBW & Run Out (~8â€“10%)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Boundaries**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Fours: ~80,000+\n",
        "\n",
        "- Sixes: ~10,000+\n",
        "\n",
        "- Ratio â†’ roughly 8:1 (fours much more frequent).\n",
        "\n",
        "- Boundary hitting trend increased after 2014.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        " **Top Batsmen (Runs Scored 2008â€“2017)**\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Virat Kohli** (~4,100 runs)\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Suresh Raina** (~4,000 runs)\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Rohit Sharma** (~3,800 runs)\n",
        "\n",
        "- **David Warner** (~3,500 runs)\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Chris Gayle** (~3,200 runs, highest sixes)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "ðŸ”¹ Strike Rates (Top by SR, min 500 balls faced)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Chris Gayle, AB de Villiers, Glenn Maxwell usually dominate with SR 150+.**\n",
        "\n",
        "**Top Bowlers (Wickets Taken 2008â€“2017)**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Lasith Malinga (~150 wickets)\n",
        "\n",
        "- Amit Mishra (~134 wickets)\n",
        "\n",
        "- Harbhajan Singh (~127 wickets)\n",
        "\n",
        "- Dwayne Bravo (~122 wickets)\n",
        "\n",
        "- Bhuvneshwar Kumar (~111 wickets)\n",
        "\n",
        "ðŸ”¹ Economy kings: Sunil Narine, Rashid Khan (later seasons) â€“ best economy ~6.5â€“7.0.\n",
        "\n",
