        " **Titles & Finals**\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Mumbai Indians** (MI) â†’ 3 titles (2013, 2015, 2017)\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Chennai Super Kings** (CSK) â†’ 2 titles (2010, 2011) + 4 finals lost\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Kolkata Knight Riders** (KKR) â†’ 2 titles (2012, 2014)\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Sunrisers Hyderabad** (SRH) â†’ 1 title (2016)\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Rajasthan Royals** (RR) â†’ 1 title (2008, inaugural champions)\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Deccan Chargers** (DC) â†’ 1 title (2009, now defunct)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Clear dominance: MI & CSK rivalry shaped the decade.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Win Consistency (2008â€“2017)**\n",
        "\n",
        "Most wins overall: Mumbai Indians (~90+).\n",
        "\n",
        "Highest win %: Chennai Super Kings (~60%).\n",
        "\n",
        "Most inconsistent team: Delhi Daredevils (frequent bottom finishes).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Toss vs Match Wins**\n",
        "\n",
        "Toss winners donâ€™t always win matches â†’ ~51% win rate only.\n",
        "\n",
        "However, fielding first after toss win gives slightly better odds (~54%).\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        " **Team Rivalries**\n",
        "\n",
        "- MI vs CSK â†’ most high-pressure finals.\n",
        "\n",
        "- RCB vs KKR â†’ highest-scoring thrillers.\n",
        "\n",
        "- MI vs KKR â†’ MI dominating head-to-head.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Home Advantage**\n",
        "\n",
        "Teams like CSK (Chepauk) and MI (Wankhede) had strong home records (~65% win rate).\n",
        "\n",
        "Neutral venues (2014 UAE leg, finals) showed reduced advantage."
